<i>Do you read me?</i>

1161
01:34:51,144 --> 01:34:54,101
<i>This is KDK 1 calling KDK 12.</i>

1162
01:34:54,271 --> 01:34:57,765
<i>KDK 1 calling KDK 12.
Are you receiv--</i>

1163
01:34:57,942 --> 01:34:59,932
[RADIO SHUTS OFF]

1164
01:35:08,912 --> 01:35:10,573
[RINGING]

1165
01:35:12,457 --> 01:35:14,323
MAN:
<i>Good evening. Forest service.</i>

1166
01:35:14,542 --> 01:35:16,783
This is Dick Hallorann again.

1167
01:35:16,961 --> 01:35:20,078
I called a while ago about
the folks at the Overlook Hotel.

1168
01:35:20,256 --> 01:35:21,246
Oh, yeah.

1169
01:35:21,423 --> 01:35:25,132
We tried to contact them several
times but they didn't answer.

1170
01:35:25,302 --> 01:35:28,921
Maybe they got their radio
turned off or they can't hear it.

1171
01:35:29,140 --> 01:35:32,006
If you'd like, I'd be glad
to try again later on.

1172
01:35:32,518 --> 01:35:34,634
That's very nice of you.

1173
01:35:34,854 --> 01:35:36,640
I'll call you back later.

1174
01:35:36,814 --> 01:35:37,849
Bye.

1175
01:36:24,945 --> 01:36:27,984
Pardon me, miss.
What time will we get to Denver?

1176
01:36:28,198 --> 01:36:30,360
We're due to arrive at 8:20, sir.

1177
01:36:30,534 --> 01:36:32,150
Thank you very much.

1178
01:36:36,373 --> 01:36:38,364
[TYPEWRITER KEYS CLACKING]

1179
01:37:26,215 --> 01:37:28,206
[PHONE RINGING]

1180
01:37:35,975 --> 01:37:36,965
Durkin's Garage.

1181
01:37:37,185 --> 01:37:38,300
DICK:
<i>Can I speak to Larry?</i>

1182
01:37:38,478 --> 01:37:39,467
Speaking.

1183
01:37:39,770 --> 01:37:42,262
Hi, Larry. This is Dick.
Dick Hallorann.

1184
01:37:42,564 --> 01:37:44,225
Dick! How you doing?

1185
01:37:44,442 --> 01:37:45,773
How's the weather down there?

1186
01:37:45,984 --> 01:37:49,148
I'm not in Florida.
I'm calling from Stapleton Airport.

1187
01:37:49,529 --> 01:37:51,112
What are you doing there?

1188
01:37:51,573 --> 01:37:54,987
I just got in from Miami.
I got to get to the Overlook today.

1189
01:37:55,203 --> 01:37:56,819
What's the weather like there?

1190
01:37:57,454 --> 01:38:00,322
The snowplows are keeping things
moving in town...

1191
01:38:00,541 --> 01:38:02,452
...but the mountain roads
are blocked.

1192
01:38:03,002 --> 01:38:05,710
Then I'm going to need a Snowcat
to get up there.

1193
01:38:05,921 --> 01:38:07,753
Can you fix me up with one?

1194
01:38:07,965 --> 01:38:10,046
What's the big deal
about getting there today...

1195
01:38:10,259 --> 01:38:11,795
...especially in this weather?

1196
01:38:12,677 --> 01:38:16,136
Larry, just between you and me,
we got a very serious problem...

1197
01:38:16,349 --> 01:38:18,590
...with the people taking care
of the place.

1198
01:38:18,810 --> 01:38:22,644
They turned out to be
completely unreliable assholes.

1199
01:38:22,854 --> 01:38:24,640
Ullman phoned me last night.

1200
01:38:24,856 --> 01:38:28,225
And I'm supposed to find out
if they have to be replaced.

1201
01:38:29,694 --> 01:38:31,731
How long will it take you
to get here?

1202
01:38:32,073 --> 01:38:33,734
About five hours.

1203
01:38:33,949 --> 01:38:36,157
I'm going to rent a car
here at the airport.

1204
01:38:36,661 --> 01:38:38,402
Okay, I'll take care of it.

1205
01:38:38,621 --> 01:38:41,453
Thanks, Larry.
I really appreciate that.

1206
01:38:41,666 --> 01:38:44,203
That's all right. Drive carefully.

1207
01:38:44,918 --> 01:38:46,909
[MUSIC PLAYS ON RADIO]

1208
01:38:49,966 --> 01:38:53,208
HAL: <i>You're with Hal and Charlie
on Radio 63, KHOW, Denver.</i>

1209
01:38:53,427 --> 01:38:56,011
<i>And we have a bad day out there.</i>

1210
01:38:56,180 --> 01:38:59,547
CHARLIE: <i>Heavy snow throughout
the Denver metro area.</i>

1211
01:38:59,766 --> 01:39:01,256
<i>Many mountain passes...</i>

1212
01:39:01,476 --> 01:39:04,344
<i>... Wolf Creek and Red Mountain
passes are closed...</i>

1213
01:39:04,521 --> 01:39:07,855
<i>...and the chain law is in effect
at the Eisenhower Tunnel.</i>

1214
01:39:08,024 --> 01:39:09,685
HAL:
<i>We hear from the news department...</i>

1215
01:39:09,902 --> 01:39:13,110
<i>...only a few flights are
landing at Stapleton Airport...</i>

1216
01:39:13,322 --> 01:39:14,904
<i>...and with storms like this...</i>

1217
01:39:15,115 --> 01:39:18,484
<i>...I guess the entire airport will
be closed within the hour.</i>

1218
01:39:18,661 --> 01:39:22,279
CHARLIE: <i>The storm will continue through
the day and the Weather Service...</i>

1219
01:39:22,497 --> 01:39:24,956
<i>...has declared a stockman's
and traveler's advisory...</i>

1220
01:39:25,167 --> 01:39:27,956
<i>...for all areas outlying
the Denver metro region.</i>

1221
01:39:28,171 --> 01:39:29,536
<i>Get the cows in the barn.</i>

1222
01:39:31,215 --> 01:39:33,296
[MUSIC PLAYS ON TV]

1223
01:39:51,027 --> 01:39:52,061
Hon?

1224
01:39:57,073 --> 01:39:59,485
Listen to me for a minute, will you?

1225
01:40:03,288 --> 01:40:06,997
I'm just going to go and
talk to Daddy for a few minutes...

1226
01:40:07,210 --> 01:40:09,247
...and I'll be right back.

1227
01:40:10,212 --> 01:40:12,750
I want you to just stay here...

1228
01:40:12,923 --> 01:40:15,416
...and watch your cartoons, okay?

1229
01:40:18,554 --> 01:40:20,010
Okay, hon?

1230
01:40:23,309 --> 01:40:26,176
<i>Yes, Mrs. Torrance.</i>

1231
01:40:34,945 --> 01:40:36,152
All right.

1232
01:40:37,030 --> 01:40:41,115
I'll-- I'll be back
in just about five minutes.

1233
01:40:41,953 --> 01:40:44,284
I'm going to lock the door
behind me.

1234
01:41:33,212 --> 01:41:34,793
Jack?

1235
01:41:55,609 --> 01:41:57,065
Jack?

1236
01:44:10,618 --> 01:44:11,654
JACK:
How do you like it?

1237
01:44:11,746 --> 01:44:13,202
[SHRIEKS]

1238
01:44:14,372 --> 01:44:15,828
Jack.

1239
01:44:18,918 --> 01:44:20,454
How do you like it?

1240
01:44:30,389 --> 01:44:33,051
What are you doing down here?

1241
01:44:37,438 --> 01:44:39,770
I just...

1242
01:44:40,231 --> 01:44:41,266
...wanted...

1243
01:44:41,692 --> 01:44:43,432
...to talk to you.

1244
01:44:45,820 --> 01:44:47,060
Okay.

1245
01:44:47,698 --> 01:44:49,154
Let's talk.

1246
01:44:58,958 --> 01:45:00,949
What do you want to talk about?

1247
01:45:06,966 --> 01:45:08,207
I....

1248
01:45:08,886 --> 01:45:12,048
I can't really remember.

1249
01:45:12,847 --> 01:45:14,963
You can't remember.

1250
01:45:15,768 --> 01:45:17,099
No...

1251
01:45:17,478 --> 01:45:18,889
...I can't.

1252
01:45:24,193 --> 01:45:27,435
JACK:
<i>Maybe it was about Danny?</i>

1253
01:45:29,823 --> 01:45:32,532
<i>Maybe it was about him.</i>

1254
01:45:36,162 --> 01:45:39,451
<i>I think we should discuss Danny.</i>

1255
01:45:42,252 --> 01:45:44,085
<i>I think...</i>

1256
01:45:44,462 --> 01:45:48,252
<i>...we should discuss
what should be done with him.</i>

1257
01:45:52,930 --> 01:45:55,546
What should be done with him?

1258
01:46:00,520 --> 01:46:02,306
I don't know.

1259
01:46:02,814 --> 01:46:04,805
I don't think that's true.

1260
01:46:05,024 --> 01:46:07,608
I think you have some
very definite ideas...

1261
01:46:07,819 --> 01:46:09,527
...about what should be done
with Danny.

1262
01:46:09,738 --> 01:46:12,320
And I'd like to know
what they are.

1263
01:46:14,243 --> 01:46:16,029
Well, I...

1264
01:46:16,328 --> 01:46:20,743
...I think maybe he should be taken
to a doctor.

1265
01:46:20,957 --> 01:46:24,246
You think "maybe"
he should be taken to a doctor?

1266
01:46:24,461 --> 01:46:25,826
Yes.

1267
01:46:26,462 --> 01:46:29,796
When do you think "maybe"
he should be taken to a doctor?

1268
01:46:30,466 --> 01:46:31,797
As soon as possible?

1269
01:46:32,427 --> 01:46:34,760
[IN HIGH-PITCHED VOICE]
"As soon as possible?"

1270
01:46:37,432 --> 01:46:38,844
Please.

1271
01:46:40,269 --> 01:46:43,511
You believe his health
